# Persistence store (docs/architecture.md §13) — the shared offline-message + durable-claim folder,
# synced between a realm's machines by whatever `persistence.dir` points at (Dropbox here).
#
# Track ONLY the skeleton: the immediate category folders, via their .gitkeep. Ignore EVERYTHING one
# level deeper — it is machine-generated runtime data that holds encrypted message bodies AND cleartext
# subjects/identities, and must never reach the public repo. (Dropbox still syncs it between machines;
# git just versions the structure.)
*/*
!*/.gitkeep
